<DOC><DOCNO> AP880322-0111 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-22-88 1229EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Liberia     03-22 0135</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Liberia,0139</SECOND><HEAD>Coup Plot Uncovered By Government</HEAD><DATELINE>MONROVIA, Liberia (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The government said Tuesday that 12 men_ including an opposition party leader _ have been arrested in aplot to overthrow the government of President Samuel Doe.   Seven coup plotters were still at large, including an armycaptain and two sergeants, said Information Minister EmmanuelBowier.   Among those arrested in the plot, which was uncovered March 16,were Gabriel Kpolleh, leader of the opposition Liberia UnificationParty, Bowier said. Four of those arrested were soldiers.   Arms, ammunition and military uniforms were found in a Monrovianeighborhood, he added.   Doe has been the target of several assassination and coupattempts. An abortive Nov. 12, 1985 coup attempt, which came afterelections that opposition leaders said were rigged, left more than600 people dead.</TEXT></DOC>